# {{.ModulePath}}

A gopernicus host application, scaffolded by `gopernicus init`. It is an
sdk-only composition root: a logger, an HTTP router with the standard
middleware, a `GET /healthz` liveness probe, and graceful shutdown. It mounts no
features yet — that is your first edit.

## What was scaffolded

```
cmd/server/main.go              composition root — wiring; the only place that names concrete adapters
Makefile                        build/vet/test/run/migrate + the host guard subset
.env.example                    environment template (copy to .env)
workshop/migrations/{{.LedgerDir}}/         host-owned migration ledger (scaffold-and-own, never-renumber){{if .HasDB}}
workshop/migrations/main.go     host-owned pre-boot migration runner (apply + -status){{end}}
```
{{if .HasDB}}
This host wires the **{{.DB}}** datastore connector. `main.go` opens it from the
environment and probes it in `/healthz`; the migration runner applies the
host-owned ledger before boot.
{{else}}
This host wires **no datastore** (`--db=none`): the store you supply — a real
connector or an in-memory implementation — is your choice when you mount a
feature.
{{end}}
## Pre-tag wiring

gopernicus publishes no version tags yet, so `go get` cannot resolve the
`github.com/gopernicus/gopernicus/*` modules this host requires. Until `v0.1.0`
is cut, point each one at a local checkout of the gopernicus repo with a replace
directive:

```
go mod edit -replace github.com/gopernicus/gopernicus/sdk=/abs/path/to/gopernicus/sdk
{{- if .HasDB}}
go mod edit -replace {{.ConnectorPath}}=/abs/path/to/gopernicus/{{.ConnectorRel}}
{{- end}}
go mod tidy
```

Then `make run` (or `go run ./cmd/server`) and hit `http://localhost:{{.Port}}/healthz`.

## Wiring a feature

A gopernicus feature reaches this host only through the narrow `feature.Mount` +
`Register` surface — no init() registration, no service locator. Add the feature
module (and its store adapter, if it persists data) to `go.mod`, add the replace
directives above for it too, then wire it in the "mount your features here"
block in `cmd/server/main.go`:

```go
mount := feature.Mount{Router: router, Logger: log}
repos := <store>.Repositories(db)        // or your own in-memory store
svc, err := <feature>.NewService(repos, <feature>.Config{ /* ... */ })
if err != nil {
	return err
}
svc.Register(mount)
```

## Migrations

Migrations are host-owned and applied pre-boot — the framework never migrates at
startup.
{{if .HasDB}}
```
gopernicus db create <slug>              # scaffold NNNN_<slug>.sql into the ledger
make migrate                             # apply pending migrations
go run ./workshop/migrations -status     # applied vs pending (file-only when the
                                         # database is unreachable)
```
{{else}}
This host has no datastore, so no runner was scaffolded. Re-run `gopernicus init
--db=turso|pgx` for a host with a migration runner.
{{end}}
